      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It is impossible for me to give you a definitive guarantee that one pill won't affect your kidneys, as your specific kidney function depends on many factors the doctors monitor. NSAIDs are flagged as a risk because they can stress already compromised kidney tissue, even if immediate failure is unlikely. Because CKD involves ongoing kidney compromise, it's best to err on the side of caution and use the acetaminophen alternative instead. Always rely on your healthcare provider for specific medical decisions regarding your condition.",
      "source": "target",
